Both are somewhat reviled: as a Siennese banker, Tolomei is treated as a second-class citizen of France; Littlefigner comes from a lowly house and is seen as a slimy brothel owner.
On the surface, neither is a player in the constant struggle for power in their respective kingdoms; however, in a way they are the ones who are truly in power, since they control their kindoms' finances.
They use blackmail as an additional means of gaining power.